From 474a86f12e811e67db99eb60a5fba90c684c75d9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jason Perlow <jperlow@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 18 May 2026 09:46:24 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] armchina-npu: MS-R1 32-bit SMMU constraint
 (FyrbyAdditive/ms-r1-npu-hack)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The NPU address bus on Minisforum MS-R1 (CIX Sky1) is 32-bit. Without
this constraint the IOMMU allocates IOVAs starting at 0x700000000 (35-bit),
which the NPU truncates — causing SMMU faults on every DMA operation.

Force bus_dma_limit=0xc0000000 and dma_mask=32 so IOVAs land in the
range [0x80000000, 0xbfffefff] that the NPU can actually address.

Source: FyrbyAdditive/ms-r1-npu-hack (BSD-2-Clause-Patent)
Fix 4 of 4 — the root cause why NPU inference was silently failing.
---
 drivers/misc/armchina-npu/aipu_mm.c | 9 ++++++---
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/misc/armchina-npu/aipu_mm.c b/drivers/misc/armchina-npu/aipu_mm.c
index 03d34a50046d..11793cd78775 100755
--- a/drivers/misc/armchina-npu/aipu_mm.c
+++ b/drivers/misc/armchina-npu/aipu_mm.c
@@ -940,12 +940,15 @@ static int aipu_mm_add_iova_region(struct aipu_memory_manager *mm)
 		iova_region_size = 0x10000000;
 	}
 
+/* MS-R1 fix: NPU address bus is 32-bit; constrain IOMMU IOVAs to 3 GB.
+ * Without this the IOMMU hands out 35-bit addresses that the NPU truncates,
+ * causing SMMU faults on every memory access. (FyrbyAdditive/ms-r1-npu-hack) */
 #if (KERNEL_VERSION(5, 5, 0) <= LINUX_VERSION_CODE)
-	mm->dev->bus_dma_limit = 0x800000000;
+	mm->dev->bus_dma_limit = 0xc0000000;
 #elif (KERNEL_VERSION(4, 19, 0) <= LINUX_VERSION_CODE)
-	mm->dev->bus_dma_mask = 0x800000000;
+	mm->dev->bus_dma_mask = 0xc0000000;
 #endif
-	mm->dma_mask = 35;
+	mm->dma_mask = 32;
 
 	if (aipu_mm_reserved_iova_for_never_map(mm, IOVA_ALLOC)) {
 		dev_err(mm->dev, "fail to reserve iova region for never map.");
-- 
